B. Liu opened a jewelry store. He intentionally marked the price of the jewelry slightly higher than the acceptable price, and then offered to give customers discounts. The customers thought that the jewelry in this store was very affordable.
C. Mr. Zhang's content was rich and humorous in the first class. The students evaluated him very well. In the second class, Mr. Zhang's lectures were tedious. The students felt that Mr. Zhang was in a bad state today, which affected his performance.
